8 FIRST SPECIAL SESSION
9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to S.P. 89, L.D. 202, “An Act to Increase the
10 Number of Children a Family Child Care Provider May Care for Without Having to Be
11 Licensed by the Department of Health and Human Services”
12 Amend the bill by striking out the title and substituting the following:
13 'An Act to Increase the Number of Children a Child Care Provider May Care for
14 Without Having to Be Licensed by the Department of Health and Human Services'
15 Amend the bill in section 1 in paragraph C in the 5th line (page 1, line 8 in L.D.) by
16 inserting after the following: "other children" the following: ','
17 Amend the bill in section 1 in paragraph C in the 5th line (page 1, line 8 in L.D.) by
18 inserting after the following: "siblings" the following: ', and no more than 3 of the total
19 number of children in the provider's care are under 2 years of age'
20 Amend the bill by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or section
21 number to read consecutively.
22 SUMMARY
2233 This amendment keeps the changes to the number of children that an unlicensed
2244 provider can care for proposed in the bill as long as no more than 3 of the total number of
2255 children in the provider's care are under 2 years of age. The amendment also changes the
2266 title to reflect the substance of the bill.
